[{"category":"section","location":"#SWRCache.jl","page":"Home","text":"SWRCache.jl provides an in-memory stale-while-revalidate cache with single-flight refresh behavior for one cached value.\n\nConstruct caches with SWRMemoryCache(fetcher) or SWRMemoryCache(fetcher, entry).","title":"SWRCache.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"#API","page":"Home","text":"","title":"API"},{"category":"section","location":"#Design-behavior","page":"Home","text":"now <= expires_at: return fresh cached value.\nexpires_at < now <= stale_until: return stale cached value and trigger background refresh.\nnow > stale_until (or cache miss): block until the single shared refresh completes.","title":"Design behavior"},{"category":"type","location":"#SWRCache.CacheEntry","page":"Home","text":"CacheEntry(value, expires_at, stale_until)\n\nRepresents one cached value and its serve-time boundaries.\n\nTime semantics:\n\nnow <= expires_at: value is fresh.\nexpires_at < now <= stale_until: value is soft-expired and may be served stale.\nnow > stale_until: value is hard-expired and must be refreshed before serving.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SWRCache.CacheEntry"},{"category":"type","location":"#SWRCache.SWRMemoryCache","page":"Home","text":"SWRMemoryCache(fetcher)\nSWRMemoryCache(fetcher, entry)\n\nConstructs an in-memory cache around a fetcher that returns CacheEntry values.\n\nfetcher must always return the same concrete CacheEntry{V} type for a given cache instance. The one-argument constructor eagerly calls fetcher once to seed the cache.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SWRCache.SWRMemoryCache"},{"category":"function","location":"#SWRCache.cache_get!","page":"Home","text":"cache_get!(cache)\n\nReturns the cached value using stale-while-revalidate semantics.\n\nFresh entries are returned immediately.\nSoft-expired entries return stale immediately if another refresh is already   in progress; otherwise, the calling task performs the refresh before returning.\nHard-expired entries (or cache misses) block and refresh before returning.\n\nRefresh work is single-flight: at most one task executes fetcher at a time.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SWRCache.cache_get!"},{"category":"function","location":"#SWRCache.refresh!","page":"Home","text":"refresh!(cache)\n\nForces a refresh under the cache lock, stores the new entry, and returns the new value.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SWRCache.refresh!"},{"category":"function","location":"#SWRCache.invalidate!","page":"Home","text":"invalidate!(cache)\n\nAtomically clears the current entry and returns true if an entry was present.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SWRCache.invalidate!"},{"category":"function","location":"#SWRCache.clear!","page":"Home","text":"clear!(cache)\n\nClears the current entry and returns cache.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SWRCache.clear!"}]
